==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Infract
<hw>In*fract"</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧n*fr⟦acr⟧kt")</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>infractus</ets>; pref. <ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>fractus</ets>. p.
p. of <ets>frangere</ets> to break.]</ety> <def>Not broken or fractured;
unharmed; whole.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chapman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infract</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Infract
<hw>In*fract"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Infracted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Infracting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>infractus</ets>, p.
p. of of <ets>infringere</ets>. See <er>Infringe</er>.]</ety> <def>To
break; to infringe.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Thomson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infractible</ent>⟦br⟧
